translated: Halldin, Gustav (Gösta) Adolf, accountant, from TroMhåttan, born on November 17, 1896 in Stockholm to engineer Adolf H. and Ingeborg Johansson. Married in 1933 to Anna Sundström, with whom he had three children: Lars (born 1933), Hans (born 1935), and Anders (born 1942). Halldin graduated from Norra Real High School in Stockholm in 1916 and received his degree in business administration from Stockholm University in 1923. He was employed by the city of Stockholm from 1917 to 1918, as an assistant with the water board in 1919, an ordinary clerk-writer there in 1920, an ordinary bookkeeper in Norrländska kraftvärden in 1932, responsible controller there in 1936, first responsible controller at Troliliätte kraftvärd in 1943, and accountant there in 1947.
